    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Resolves that Congress must meet its constitutional obligation to provide for the common defense of the United States by restoring spending cuts required by sequestration. (Sequestration is a process of automatic, usually across-the-board spending reductions under which budgetary resources are permanently cancelled to enforce specific budget policy goals.)</p> <p>Resolves that Congress should enact legislation that: </p> <ul> <li> restores no less than 75% of the pre-sequester levels established by the Budget Control Act of 2011,</li> <li>offsets the increases in discretionary spending through a combination of reductions to mandatory spending and increases in revenue, </li> <li>includes a Chained Consumer Price Index for Social Security and further means testing for Medicare, and </li> <li>increases revenue by closing tax loopholes and capping deductions for high-income households. </li> </ul>]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
